OL,5,Clater
OL,7,F"We were ostracised," he recalls.
OL,8,F"People didn't want to know us.
OL,9,FFinancially, it ruined us. We nearly
OL,10,Flost everything we had worked for all
OL,11,Four lives. People thought we were
OL,12,Fcriminals."
OL,14,FSue is still too traumatised to talk
OL,15,Fabout it. But Peter, accompanied by
OL,16,Fhis daughter Sam, agreed make the
OL,17,Fdifficult journey back to Dorset with
OL,18,Fus to see the people and the Post
OL,19,FOffice he hasn't set eyes on for over
OL,20,Fa decade.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G5/14
