OL,5,Clater
OL,7,F"They are just wicked people. We were
OL,8,Fdoing our best to make their business
OL,9,Fa success and they just stabbed us in
OL,10,Fthe back and threw us away like dirt."
OL,12,FTheir previously perfect life here, he
OL,13,Fsays, was then made even more
OL,14,Fdifficult by the fact that many of his
OL,15,Fcustomers and neighbours trusted the
OL,16,FPost Office rather than believing him.
OL,18,FAs we drove into the village of West
OL,19,FLulworth, he admitted that he was
OL,20,Ffeeling apprehensive about how he
OL,21,Fwould be greeted after all this time.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G8/14
