OL,5,Clater
OL,7,F"If you're honest with yourself, you
OL,8,Fknow there's that ` at the back of
OL,9,Fyour mind ` even if it was your own
OL,10,Fchildren, at the back of your mind,
OL,11,Fyou'd have thought ` 'is there a
OL,12,Fpossibility?' With such a trusted
OL,13,Finstitution as the Post Office, it's
OL,14,Fwhat made that germ of doubt."
OL,16,FDave's wife, Elaine, agrees. "There is
OL,17,Fa phrase," she says, "there's no smoke
OL,18,Fwithout fire."
OL,20,FPeter says he feels "incredibly
OL,21,Fbitter" towards the Post Office now.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G    G10/14
